Iranian students are prepared to die for their country's nuclear program.
They created a shield.
Several hundred college students have created a living shield around a nuclear facility in Iran.
They want to express their support for their country’s nuclear program against a possible Israeli attack.
The students prayed in front of the building at noon on Tuesday and then called for the deaths of the U.S. and Israel.
Several hundred university students in Isfahan, Iran, created a live shield around the Isfahan Nuclear Technology Center on Tuesday, where uranium is being processed.
They show that they are ready to defend the nuclear program of their countries with their own lives.
The International Atomic Energy Agency (IAEA) said in a recent report that Iran did not seem to have stopped pursuing a nuclear weapon.
There is talk of a possible attack on Iran's nuclear facilities in Israel.
