She then explained the new post of High Representative for Foreign Affairs and Security Policy as an answer to the question: "Who is this European Union? To which phone number should I call?", a significant step towards unification and greater readability of EU policy towards countries such as China or India.
No one wants to ban cheese.
Vicenová also addressed the agenda that the European Council lived, lives and will live in the near future.
The Czech Presidency was a success.
The Czechs solved the coming financial crisis, solved the gas crisis or held a summit for the Eastern Partnership.
The fall of the government at this time was described as a major negative, which damaged the Czech Republic very badly.
Czech representation in the EU is currently very busy.
In the words of the Ambassador, the 'frank' was not only the Presidency, but also the subsequent financial crisis, which is still being addressed today.
Moreover, the new seven-year budget of the Union still needs to be approved, which is becoming much more complicated precisely because of the current economic situation.
