He owes contributions to projects
Social projects, which are part of programs such as Habitat, Saving Public Places and 3x1 for migrants, face the risk of not being completed or they will be very late due to lack of economic resources, Miguel Ángel López Miranda said.
The director of urban social development said that if the construction work has gone forward so far, there is now a risk that the state government will not be able to provide the relevant supplies, which require funds of more than 11 million pesos on three programs.
He stated that the total investment in these three programs is almost 50 million pesos. The state accounts for 25%. By this time, only the Federation and the city have supplied funds for the work, so it is possible that there will be a delay in the implementation of projects.
