They gave him a last goodbye.
With Felipe Bacio Cortés, Lt. Col. of the Mexican Air Force, we said goodbye to all the honors that Governor Jorge Torres López, citizens and the government of the state, the Mexican Army through the Sixth Military Zone, the Mexican Air Force itself, the leaders and students of Saltillo Technological High School, where he studied in 1985 and where he excelled in both study and sport.
Bacio Cortés died in recent days after the helicopter he was driving crashed. Also on board was the Cabinet Secretary, José Francisco Blake Mora, and six other persons, all officials of this state.
At 6:05 p.m., the remains of Saltillen native Bacio Cortés (burned) arrived to be handed over through funeral service to the Mexican Air Force under Major Jaime Martinez in the area where, meanwhile, the family, his daughter Amanda and wife Cristina, mother, siblings and other relatives, students and teachers had gathered.
